Package: CohortIntelligence
Title: OHDSI-Native Cohort Exploration and Hypothesis Generation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Minqi", "Xiong",
           email = "mxiong5@jhu.edu",
           role  = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: An OHDSI-native cohort exploration and hypothesis-generation
    workbench for OMOP CDM studies. Designed to fill the gap between
    aggregate cohort diagnostics (CohortDiagnostics, ATLAS) and formal
    chart review. Accepts cohorts defined by ATLAS JSON files (via CirceR)
    or pre-instantiated cohort tables. Key capabilities include: (1) reactive
    quilt plot -- a patient x domain x time-window heatmap giving a bird's-eye
    view of the cohort; (2) unsupervised ML pipeline -- UMAP dimensionality
    reduction ('uwot'), k-means/hierarchical clustering ('cluster'), and
    isolation-forest anomaly scoring ('isotree') to detect subgroups and
    out-of-distribution patients; (3) signal explanation -- per-patient
    priority explanation cards with severity-tagged findings; (4) cluster
    profile summaries -- cautious descriptive labels, prevalence comparisons,
    and narrative summaries per cluster; (5) review sets -- eight guided
    patient groups to structure chart review workflows; (6) temporal rule
    flags -- rule-based detection of structured-data patterns that warrant
    clinical review; (7) clinician meeting report export -- self-contained
    HTML packet covering cohort landscape, cluster profiles, review sets,
    temporal flags, and candidate hypotheses. All outputs are
    hypothesis-generating and require clinical validation; this tool does
    NOT replace CohortDiagnostics, ATLAS, or formal chart review. Designed
    for OMOP CDM v5.3/5.4. ML packages required:
    install.packages(c('uwot', 'cluster', 'isotree')).
